==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dedimus
<hw>Ded"i*mus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>dedimus</ets> we have given, fr. <ets>dare</ets> to give. So called
because the writ began, <ets>Dedimus potestatem</ets>, etc.]</ety>
<fld>(Law)</fld> <def>A writ to commission private persons to do some
act in place of a judge, as to examine a witness, etc.</def>
<rj><au>Bouvier.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dedition</ent>⟦br⟧
